  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Get ready for an adventure and discover all the magic that Europe has to offer. Our challenging walking holidays will suit those who enjoy an energetic pace and exhilarating views, who are looking to explore beyond the beaten track.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13093746/challenging-hero.png?width=216&amp;height=21" alt="challenging walking holidays" data-udi="umb://media/3ba12c494430493498ec0267c083c192" /></span></p>
<h2>What to expect from our challenging walking holidays</h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We're experts in challenging walking holidays. Our guides know the best routes and show you around lesser-known gems, so that you can really get to grips with somewhere new.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our challenging walking holidays will take you on exhilarating high alpine treks, through incredible landscapes and up some of Europe’s highest peaks.</span></p>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Free guided walks included in your holiday</h3>
<p><img src="/media/13093530/close-up-feet.png?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" /></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">We offer free guided walks in select resorts, run by local experts who will help you make the most of your holiday.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">We'll guide you through some of the best parts of each location with insider tips and tricks. </span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Our self-guided walking holidays offer total flexibility</h3>
<p><img src="/media/13093531/close-up-walking.png?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" /></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You'll be free to explore on your own terms. Whether you want to take a leisurely stroll or try something more strenuous.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">You'll have the support of our resort representatives to offer advice and tips if you need it. </span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>See more, do more and discover more</h3>
<p><img style="width: autopx; height: 100%;" src="/media/13080490/merano-tourist-board-image-8.jpg?width=500&amp;height=268.49642004773267" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/ddef516ea88a4726b9a4ac183045b915" /></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you travel with us you'll experience a lot more than on a typical walking holiday. </span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">We've chosen our European resorts for their culture and cuisine, as well as their endless activities and sights.</span></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
<h2>Discover our popular resorts for challenging walking holidays</h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Get ready to pack! Here is your chance to explore Europe's most beautiful destinations and lesser-known resorts. Immerse yourself in the sublime atmosphere of Europe's amazing coastlines, test your stamina on some steep and tough terrain, and challenge yourself while enjoying this unforgettable journey.</span></p>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>St.Anton &amp; Lech, Austria</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13093747/st-anton.png?width=132&amp;height=21" alt="walking holidays" data-udi="umb://media/a709200e6b7049f7ab15c51703537f66" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The resorts of St.Anton and Lech have lots of high-alpine routes and spectacular scenery. Lech has free lifts, so access to higher routes is easy. The picturesque resort town of St. Anton is considered one of the most beautiful mountain towns in the Alps, offering spectacular views from its many peaks, gorges and scenic hiking trails.</span></p>
<p><strong>St.Anton &amp; Lech walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Sattelkopf Mountain, St.Anton</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">This challenging walk is for the adventurous. Head from St.Anton up to Verwall and then take trail 18 up to the peak of Sattelkopf before returning down to Trischalpe and Moostal back to St.Anton. The views are incredible from the summit and the hut at Tritschalpe makes a lovely refreshment stop.</span></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Hasenfluh &amp; Zurser Lake Loop:</strong> <span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a hiking route for experienced walkers looking for a full day out in the mountains. There are some difficult uphill sections, but all the effort is worth it! The hike begins in the Zürs ski area and takes you to one of the most popular destinations in Lech am Arlberg: The Hasenfluh. </span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/7f056630899e45e8b8e0eef21334f8ef" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7f056630899e45e8b8e0eef21334f8ef}" title="St. Anton">Find out more about St.Anton &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/f5a2404579b84c448ac2a43bfaacfdd0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a2404579b84c448ac2a43bfaacfdd0}" title="Lech"><strong>Find out more about Lech &gt;&gt;</strong></a></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Zermatt, Switzerland</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: autopx;" src="/media/13065923/valentin-flauraud.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/41b4fc9eb2924f068a58bcfaaca28ec7" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The lush green meadows and wooded areas around Zermatt offer a variety of hiking and walking trails with varying degrees of difficulty and distance. Whether you’re looking for an easy stroll or a challenging route that borders on alpine mountaineering, Zermatt offers an unforgettable walking experience.</span></p>
<p><strong>Zermatt walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Randa Suspension Bridge</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">Take the Matterhorn Gotthard Bahn down to Randa, and then climb your way up a steep path to the suspension bridge. The 80m-high bridge is the largest pedestrian suspension bridge in the world, taking over 10 minutes to cross. If you like heights, this hike is for you.</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> </span></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Platthorn/Mettelhorn</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">This is a great challenging hike up the side of the Zermatt valley. The start is next to the church and it goes first to the Edelweiss Hut. From there, it continues steeply up to Trift valley until it reaches the Trift Hut. Soon after, the path steeply winds its way up towards Platthorn summit at 3345 metres. It is a straightforward walk across a permanent snow field, and then a final scramble up 75 metres to Mettelhorn summit. </span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722}" title="Zermatt">Find out more about Zermatt &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Chamonix, France</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13089916/lac-blanc-walk-chamonix-501x239.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/23b93cb064c34d90b173188e771b6107" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Chamonix Valley is a popular walking destination in France. It is nestled against the borders of Italy and Switzerland and boasts over 350 kilometres of well maintained hiking trails within its valley. Whether you’re scaling the highest peak in the region (Mont Blanc), circumnavigating its base or simply admiring it from afar, there’s never a shortage of adventure.</span></p>
<p><strong>Chamonix walking highlights</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Bel-Lachat from Chamonix</strong>: Trekking in the Alps is a must for anyone who’s interested in exploring the great outdoors. Venture into this beautiful and challenging walk with panoramic views of Mont Blanc, the Mont Blanc Massif and surrounding peaks.  </span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Grand Balcon Nord Hike:</strong> If you're looking for an exhilarating hike, this is one of the most spectacular in Chamonix. Follow a zigzag path behind the station, up to the Grand Balcon Nord which offers incredible views down over Chamonix. </span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix">Find out more about Chamonix &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>San Cassiano, Italy</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13091936/dolomites-mountains-500x270.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/e6c61abcf483420db9ba37aa21e33ea7" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Take on one of our challenging trails in the San Cassiano mountains and climb, explore and learn about this beautiful region. The excellent gondola and chairlift network makes this easy to do, with free public transport for getting you up and down the valley.</span></p>
<p><strong>San Cassiano walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>The Alta Via 1 of the Dolomites (High Path)</strong>: If you're looking for a challenging hike that will take you through beautiful scenery and allow you to explore the area, try this 12.6-km point-to-point trail. The Alta Via 1 of the Dolomites, also called the High Path or the Alpine Path, is a trail that is 125 kilometers long and climbs 7,300 meters in altitude, consisting of 12 segments from Lake Braies (BZ) to Belluno.</span></p>
</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>San Cassiano to Piz de Surega:</strong> This hike, located in Val Badia, begins at the Piz Sorega cable car station in San Cassiano. From there, it heads up a gravel road to Ütia Malga Saraghes and continues across beautiful mountain meadows to the Pralongià mountain inn.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/edb6d2efa6f64ef5bd925f12684524d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/edb6d2efa6f64ef5bd925f12684524d1}" title="San Cassiano">Find out more about San Cassiano &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
